" read-only configuration option that contains the ``SYSCONFDIR`` value "
"specified at build time relative to the installation prefix. The "
"``$TS_ROOT`` environment variable can be used alter the installation "
"prefix at run time."
msgstr ""

# ee790621cfbb4707813d3da2b7a7a059
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:182
msgid ""
"The facility used to record system log files. Refer to :ref"
":`understanding-traffic-server-log-files`."
msgstr ""

# 36287e78471c4bc7a8334fcc64866521
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:186
msgid ""
"The signal sent to :program:`traffic_cop`'s managed processes to stop "
"them."
msgstr ""

# bc59faf3199d4f87a8cce99aa4f19808
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:188
msgid "A value of ``0`` means no signal will be sent."
msgstr ""

# be7feb82a22e4c588415791fc9f1011a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:192
msgid ""
"The minimum amount of free memory space allowed before Traffic Server "
"stops the :program:`traffic_server` and :program:`traffic_manager` "
"processes to prevent the system from hanging."
msgstr ""

# 3083906361004793b0ffb94ab28d5624
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:198
msgid ""
"The minimum amount of free swap space allowed before Traffic Server stops"
" the :program:`traffic_server` and :program:`traffic_manager` processes "
"to prevent the system from hanging. This configuration variable applies "
"if swap is enabled in Linux 2.2 only."
msgstr ""

# 7aea9ea4260a422097b717235d40b608
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:205
msgid ""
"The minimum amount of addtional duration allowed before Traffic Server "
"detects that the :program:`traffic_server` is not responsive and attempts"
" a restart during startup. This configuration variable allows Traffic "
"Server a longer init time to load potentially large configuration files "
"such as remap config. Note that this applies only during startup of "
"Traffic Server and does not apply to the run time heartbeat checking."
msgstr ""

# 8cbfb72e79344eed90c36ef88bbd901a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:214
msgid ""
"The name and location of the file that contains warnings, status "
"messages, and error messages produced by the Traffic Server processes. If"
" no path is specified, then Traffic Server creates the file in its "
"logging directory."
msgstr ""

# 498c73b0aed24759864c3aa7421f3687
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:220
msgid ""
"Specifies how the output log is rolled. You can specify the following "
"values:"
