#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:719
msgid "You can specify one of the following:"
msgstr ""

# 4b3f65a4c4c84e3e8aa7dea0dce12dc4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:712
msgid ""
"``0`` ATS buffer the request until the post body has been recieved and "
"then send the request to origin."
msgstr ""

# fe60e0fcbb594871b4e73884f5b031b6
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:713
msgid ""
"``1`` immediately return a 100 Continue from ATS without waiting for the "
"post body"
msgstr ""

# fcc45490a0b2473ca35b9c0f8323e8ab
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:721
msgid "``0`` no Server: header is added to the response."
msgstr ""

# 89b8b6ad48384bc5a3a7197b2cb0d31c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:722
msgid "``1`` the Server: header is added (see string below)."
msgstr ""

# 183eee287fb64d4ebb9fc52926391bd7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:723
msgid ""
"``2`` the Server: header is added only if the response from origin does "
"not have one already."
msgstr ""

# 84084c0306064d0ca87e610f43467850
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:729
msgid ""
"This option specifies whether Traffic Server should insert an ``Age`` "
"header in the response. The Age field value is the cache's estimate of "
"the amount of time since the response was generated or revalidated by the"
" origin server."
msgstr ""

# 2ab9ba65006c4db1b34424e0508604e2
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:732
msgid "``0`` no ``Age`` header is added"
msgstr ""

# 28b3e7eab3e04772b7cfab2ee92d635e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:733
msgid "``1`` the ``Age`` header is added"
msgstr ""

# 65bfd7380df348a1a3815e6e52756847
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:739
msgid ""
"The Server: string that ATS will insert in a response header (if "
"requested, see above). Note that the current version number is always "
"appended to this string."
msgstr ""

# d16baed5c6be494bb67e9e2155bc7c2b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:745
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) ``.com`` domain expansion. This "
"configures the Traffic Server to resolve unqualified hostnames by "
"prepending with ``www.`` and appending with ``.com`` before redirecting "
"to the expanded address. For example: if a client makes a request to "
"``host``, then Traffic Server redirects the request to ``www.host.com``."
msgstr ""

# cbaa7e688a7947c39525edda25f052aa
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:753
msgid "Specifies whether Traffic Sever can generate a chunked response:"
msgstr ""

# 0dbf8028e57544bc9dc71805ed738380
# 234e5cdabac94058ab95d5336e3be7db
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:755
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:775
msgid "``0`` Never"
msgstr ""

# 189616e5f6eb446a8067344fe9b1d790
# 5cd49ca630a447e78e0c7198e2aa4d72
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:756
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:776
msgid "``1`` Always"
msgstr ""

# 3fa96e7046294e26b405032c5b60be1d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:757
msgid ""
"``2`` Generate a chunked response if the server has returned HTTP/1.1 "
"before"
msgstr ""

# 9c68ea8400ba4e5a9a65d017c85392cb
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:758
msgid ""
"``3`` = Generate a chunked response if the client request is HTTP/1.1 and"
" the origin server has returned HTTP/1.1 before"
msgstr ""

# a2e4a27acf9c4b9e84ab5ed6dd8d0457
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:762
msgid ""
"If HTTP/1.1 is used, then Traffic Server can use keep-alive connections "
"with pipelining to origin servers. If HTTP/0.9 is used, then Traffic "
"Server does not use ``keep-alive`` connections to origin servers. If "
"HTTP/1.0 is used, then Traffic Server can use ``keep-alive`` connections "
"without pipelining to origin servers."
msgstr ""

# 7f902304f4e54c65aea2cae428260a34
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:773
msgid ""
"Specifies when and how Traffic Sever uses HTTP/1.1 to communicate with "
"the origin server"
msgstr ""

# a1dbf0d24ca74de39673a53c4c156783
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:777
msgid "``2`` If the server has returned HTTP/1.1 before"
msgstr ""

# 85a973859aca4cf3ac48f744aeb490f8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:778
msgid ""
"``3`` If the client request is HTTP/1.1 and the server has returned "
"HTTP/1.1 before"
msgstr ""

# 6f8781b9f07f457d8a8a2150a916e16a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:782
msgid ""
"If :ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.use_client_target_addr` is set to 1, options"
" 2 and 3 cause the proxy to use the client HTTP version for upstream "
"requests."
msgstr ""

# 0ff0db035bd145b0be6a003f8091ef31
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:787
msgid ""
"If enabled (``1``) anytime a request contains a (``Authorization``), "
"(``Proxy-Authorization``) or (``Www-Authenticate``) header the connection"
" will be closed and not reused. This marks the connection as private. "
"When disabled (``0``) the connection will be available for reuse."
msgstr ""

# 6e638691dfbe4b17bfdef36cecd376fd
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:793
msgid ""
"Enable and set the ability to re-use server connections across client "
"connections. The valid values are"
msgstr ""

# a9dce4b709af48c2aa11284238431720
# c368b7dfeda940fcb30a9441dfab4d61
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:796
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1993
msgid "none"
msgstr ""

# 94a71624146c438e926412fbcaf1f928
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:796
msgid "Do not match, do not re-use server sessions."
msgstr ""

# 61c7666c5fd44715bb5a457753ee7e88
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:799
msgid "ip"
msgstr ""

# bf9f0caf31db416f9155929b96208ca8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:799
msgid ""
"Re-use server sessions, check only that the IP address and port of the "
"origin server matches."
msgstr ""

# 5206653598d3408082fdf157d5f4d24a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:802
msgid "host"
msgstr ""

# 1bb3f1ece645401b930507cd51388544
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:802
msgid ""
"Re-use server sessions, check only that the fully qualified domain name "
"matches."
msgstr ""

# 6035024c347a4784915e5fe916f5f9bd
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:805
msgid "both"
msgstr ""

# 426c3211d7c1495e866fb1d39c923374
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:805
msgid ""
"Re-use server sessions, but only if the IP address and fully qualified "
"domain name match."
msgstr ""

# ee218d0db3d34e268979b2a4bebfde95
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:807
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended to use either *none* or *both* for this value "
"unless you have a specific need to use *ip* or *host*. The most common "
"reason is virtual hosts that share an IP address in which case "
"performance can be enhanced if those sessions can be re-used. However, "
"not all web servers support requests for different virtual hosts on the "
"same connection so use with caution."
msgstr ""

# a51d9218f9bc41f19dc53a5372d57699
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:816
msgid ""
"Control the scope of server session re-use if it is enabled by "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.server_session_sharing.match`. The valid values"
" are"
msgstr ""

# abffe8171dc64866ba290d9d7671a149
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:819
msgid "global"
msgstr ""

# dd054914623e48e587b9eb4d6329402e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:819
msgid "Re-use sessions from a global pool of all server sessions."
msgstr ""

# e66ffe804f4847c8ba9074e0da55adb7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:821
msgid "thread"
msgstr ""

# 27939c0927f641dd87fa92c1b73180f9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:822
msgid "Re-use sessions from a per-thread pool."
msgstr ""

# e1b7c66b7c6f4685aaed9e7f6fbce7a3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:826
msgid "Control the re-use of an server session by a user agent (client) session."
msgstr ""

# 22d7f505c4d84b0c957012d1877fdc56
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:828
msgid ""
"If a user agent performs more than one HTTP transaction on its connection"
" to Traffic Server a server session must be obtained for the second (and "
"subsequent) transaction as for the first. This settings affects how that "
"server session is selected."
msgstr ""

# 2af8c0b34b3d43eb80a9ee489fd840e4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:832
msgid ""
"If this setting is ``0`` then after the first transaction the server "
"session for that transaction is released to the server pool (if any). "
"When a server session is needed for subsequent transactions one is "
"selected from the server pool or created if there is no suitable server "
"session in the pool."
msgstr ""

# 8984af8e6b7f44f9b1e69d2ca8ae0778
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:836
msgid ""
"If this setting is not ``0`` then the current server session for the user"
" agent session is \"sticky\". It will be preferred to any other server "
"session (either from the pool or newly created). The server session will "
"be detached from the user agent session only if it cannot be used for the"
" transaction. This is determined by the "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.server_session_sharing.match` value. If the "
"server session matches the next transaction according to this setting "
"then it will be used, otherwise it will be released to the pool and a "
"different session selected or created."
msgstr ""

# 839351f32836472a975dc7791a9b5ade
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:846
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) :program:`traffic_cop` heartbeat "
"logging."
msgstr ""

# e999dd3e4f3e41178fb27e93306f296b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:850
msgid ""
"For fully transparent ports use the same origin server address as the "
"client."
msgstr ""

# 9747e44022264adbbd28998f7a87c198
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:852
msgid ""
"This option causes Traffic Server to avoid where possible doing DNS "
"lookups in forward transparent proxy mode. The option is only effective "
"if the following three conditions are true -"
msgstr ""

# d75c19b34e7c429ba39454c584f30722
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:856
msgid "Traffic Server is in forward proxy mode."
msgstr ""

# d865b73a224b4a95962d6384a7f3f997
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:857
msgid "The proxy port is inbound transparent."
msgstr ""

# e3ce93e31e7a42fd976ab5f14e75e904
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:858
msgid "The target URL has not been modified by either remapping or a plugin."
msgstr ""

# 03f04cb835c0432d8ea18ffa048ea838
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:860
msgid ""
"If any of these conditions are not true, then normal DNS processing is "
"done for the connection."
msgstr ""

# 38f27d5d76c74b70ad7d333928dadbc2
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:863
msgid ""
"There are three valid values. *  0 - Disables the feature. *  1 - Enables"
" the feature with address verification.  The Proxy does the regular DNS "
"processing.  If the client-specified origin address is not in the set of "
"addresses found by the Proxy, the request continues to the client "
"specified address, but the result is not cached. *  2 - Enables the "
"feature with no address verification.  No DNS processing is performed.  "
"The result is cached (if allowed otherwise).  This option is vulnerable "
"to cache poisoning if an incorrect Host header is specified, so this "
"option should be used with extreme caution.  See bug TS-2954 for details."
msgstr ""

# de40dc828bc444aba6606e16cd030f8c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:875
msgid ""
"If all of these conditions are met, then the origin server IP address is "
"retrieved from the original client connection, rather than through HostDB"
" or DNS lookup. In effect, client DNS resolution is used instead of "
"Traffic Server DNS."
msgstr ""

# d89b9c02f1fc41e19a3976a42a737f92
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:880
msgid ""
"This can be used to be a little more efficient (looking up the target "
"once by the client rather than by both the client and Traffic Server) but"
" the primary use is when client DNS resolution can differ from that of "
"Traffic Server. Two known uses cases are:"
msgstr ""

# b5ef1672ca994bb6b42cb078e24954cc
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:885
msgid ""
"Embedded IP addresses in a protocol with DNS load sharing. In this case, "
"even though Traffic Server and the client both make the same request to "
"the same DNS resolver chain, they may get different origin server "
"addresses. If the address is embedded in the protocol then the overall "
"exchange will fail. One current example is Microsoft Windows update, "
"which presumably embeds the address as a security measure."
msgstr ""

# 671481065c45476984ac22cd011cb3c8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:893
msgid ""
"The client has access to local DNS zone information which is not "
"available to Traffic Server. There are corporate nets with local DNS "
"information for internal servers which, by design, is not propagated "
"outside the core corporate network. Depending a network topology it can "
"be the case that Traffic Server can access the servers by IP address but "
"cannot resolve such addresses by name. In such as case the client "
"supplied target address must be used."
msgstr ""

# f82677430e8245478472cf9bd21d9b0c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:902
msgid ""
"This solution must be considered interim. In the longer term, it should "
"be possible to arrange for much finer grained control of DNS lookup so "
"that wildcard domain can be set to use Traffic Server or client "
"resolution. In both known use cases, marking specific domains as client "
"determined (rather than a single global switch) would suffice. It is "
"possible to do this crudely with this flag by enabling it and then use "
"identity URL mappings to re-disable it for specific domains."
msgstr ""

# 853dc3f40c2e4475a6dc684028ddda40
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:914
msgid "Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) incoming keep-alive connections."
msgstr ""

# c2dd3ecffdab4757992d1a75c9f04c09
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:919
msgid "Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) outgoing keep-alive connections."
msgstr ""

# cca6c0f57e764e1bbdfcbc3304a54e0a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:922
msgid ""
"Enabling keep-alive does not automatically enable purging of keep-alive "
"requests when nearing the connection limit, that is controlled by "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.server_max_connections`."
msgstr ""

# 04c09fa1f4b94e6cbbf3f853c1253ade
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:929
msgid ""
"Controls wether new POST requests re-use keep-alive sessions (``1``) or "
"create new connections per request (``0``)."
msgstr ""

# 2a42575b46634442810bfbe3b1eacdc6
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:934
msgid ""
"Allows you to return a 405 Method Not Supported with Posts also "
"containing an Expect: 100-continue."
msgstr ""

# db394cfc9d724ddaa4e108951a4a3ab8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:937
msgid ""
"When a Post w/ Expect: 100-continue is blocked the stat "
"proxy.process.http.disallowed_post_100_continue will be incremented."
msgstr ""

# 1f2628046ae94a479f3bc26eac47318f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:941
msgid "Parent Proxy Configuration"
msgstr ""

# 02e3951318ea493c8750d2a9de9a7497
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:946
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) the parent caching option. Refer to "
":ref:`admin-hierarchical-caching`."
msgstr ""

# 78226fb63ed448fdb5ab385a3d123e20
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:951
msgid ""
"The amount of time allowed between connection retries to a parent cache "
"that is unavailable."
msgstr ""

# e47c81437af340a39c8b2ba212cf78e1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:956
msgid ""
"The number of times the connection to the parent cache can fail before "
"Traffic Server considers the parent unavailable."
msgstr ""

# ed2a54387b6a473e810de872833fc5c9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:961
msgid ""
"The total number of connection attempts allowed to a parent cache before "
"Traffic Server bypasses the parent or fails the request (depending on the"
" ``go_direct`` option in the :file:`parent.config` file)."
msgstr ""

# 813a06eb056e4112aff486c644c8d4e4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:967
msgid ""
"The total number of connection attempts allowed per parent, if multiple "
"parents are used."
msgstr ""

# 9a91199b42134c7fac1a1d8d0e26aa7f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:972
msgid "The timeout value (in seconds) for parent cache connection attempts."
msgstr ""

# 00e752e6332640808cb7b4230b1f128f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:978
msgid ""
"Configures Traffic Server to send proxy authentication headers on to the "
"parent cache."
msgstr ""

# 59a82b2bf77c41aaae1dd818fa05d09a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:983
msgid ""
"Don't try to resolve DNS, forward all DNS requests to the parent. This is"
" off (``0``) by default."
msgstr ""

# 2dc6b494b4884e7f85456f47061f1a37
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:986
msgid "HTTP Connection Timeouts"
msgstr ""

# 38ffea37db5a42f4b417edd8b6630e73
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:992
msgid ""
"Specifies how long Traffic Server keeps connections to clients open for a"
" subsequent request after a transaction ends. A value of ``0`` will "
"disable the no activity timeout."
msgstr ""

# 0e19f76ac0d0457484965f8e8f52ddab
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1000
msgid ""
"Specifies how long Traffic Server keeps connections to origin servers "
"open for a subsequent transfer of data after a transaction ends. A value "
"of ``0`` will disable the no activity timeout."
msgstr ""

# 2591667c68814a4284f8eab22f1f0297
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1008
msgid ""
"Specifies how long Traffic Server keeps connections to clients open if a "
"transaction stalls."
msgstr ""

# 841c7effc5a6436db147b90aded52fae
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1014
msgid ""
"Specifies how long Traffic Server keeps connections to origin servers "
"open if the transaction stalls."
msgstr ""

# 4fd509161bb44c438f89f850f97dd674
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1019
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of time Traffic Server can remain connected to a "
"client. If the transfer to the client is not complete before this timeout"
" expires, then Traffic Server closes the connection."
msgstr ""

# f91db0ace9a548409c7c5454bf4ac0d5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1022
msgid "The value of ``0`` specifies that there is no timeout."
msgstr ""

# ceab6c643cd44d04b0888ffd45a57b04
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1028
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of time Traffic Server waits for fulfillment of a "
"connection request to an origin server. If Traffic Server does not "
"complete the transfer to the origin server before this timeout expires, "
"then Traffic Server terminates the connection request."
msgstr ""

# 34d8252c4f1e431497e5a59cb4856dac
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1031
msgid "The default value of ``0`` specifies that there is no timeout."
msgstr ""

# 0c83d8755084475ab9d2d5a67bfead76
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1036
msgid ""
"The timeout interval in seconds before Traffic Server closes a connection"
" that has no activity."
msgstr ""

# b4308a3087ce44d6acaea759584207fc
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1042
msgid ""
"Specifies how long Traffic Server continues a background fill before "
"giving up and dropping the origin server connection."
msgstr ""

# e0e0e2719f524fc79abf9822c8d6291e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1048
msgid ""
"The proportion of total document size already transferred when a client "
"aborts at which the proxy continues fetching the document from the origin"
" server to get it into the cache (a **background fill**)."
msgstr ""

# db3d87e8bd464f008eb66419c8970b28
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1052
msgid "HTTP Redirection"
msgstr ""

# 590057caf9b949c98a6ebc5ada5ff099
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1056
msgid ""
"This setting indicates whether Trafficserver does a redirect follow "
"location on receiving a 3XX Redirect response from the Origin server. The"
" redirection attempt is transparent to the client and the client is "
"served the final response from the redirected-to location."
msgstr ""

# f91bd9c0fce3472ab8b20f3e538a16c4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1062
msgid ""
"This setting determines the maximum number of times Trafficserver does a "
"redirect follow location on receiving a 3XX Redirect response for a given"
" client request."
msgstr ""

# a116471181614d2e8b12857e21fa4262
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1067
msgid ""
"This setting enables Trafficserver to not include the port in the Host "
"header in the redirect follow request for default/standard ports (e.g. 80"
" for HTTP and 443 for HTTPS). Note that the port is still included in the"
" Host header if it's non-default."
msgstr ""

# a129927e991d493c905ec44dba68d069
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1072
msgid ""
"This setting enables Trafficserver to allow using original request cache "
"key (for example, set using a TS API) during a 3xx redirect follow. The "
"default behavior (0) is to use the URL specified by Location header in "
"the 3xx response as the cache key."
msgstr ""

# f7e1f2236f724e3a8106fdf35a4c0ff7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1076
msgid "Origin Server Connect Attempts"
msgstr ""

# 214182a958474a5ebdb15f96a2aa9b51
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1082
msgid ""
"The maximum number of connection retries Traffic Server can make when the"
" origin server is not responding. Each retry attempt lasts for "
"`proxy.config.http.connect_attempts_timeout`_ seconds.  Once the maximum "
"number of retries is reached, the origin is marked dead.  After this, the"
" setting  `proxy.config.http.connect_attempts_max_retries_dead_server`_ "
"is used to limit the number of retry attempts to the known dead origin."
msgstr ""

# b6c947e2ccdf4b47bf9aeeffb649d8c5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1091
msgid ""
"Maximum number of connection retries Traffic Server can make while an "
"origin is marked dead.  Typically this value is smaller than "
"`proxy.config.http.connect_attempts_max_retries`_ so an error is returned"
" to the client faster and also to reduce the load on the dead origin. The"
" timeout interval `proxy.config.http.connect_attempts_timeout`_ in "
"seconds is used with this setting."
msgstr ""

# e8585ead648346b28ddca75a0106e1e9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1098
msgid ""
"Limits the number of socket connections across all origin servers to the "
"value specified. To disable, set to zero (``0``)."
msgstr ""

# 83a3bc0b691c4e46a68e9570a0ed87ff
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1101
msgid ""
"This value is used in determining when and if to prune active origin "
"sessions. Without this value set connections to origins can consume all "
"the way up to ts:cv:`proxy.config.net.connections_throttle` connections, "
"which in turn can starve incoming requests from available connections."
msgstr ""

# bdd159ca88b64fdf9b2358c0283f7a20
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1109
msgid ""
"Limits the number of socket connections per origin server to the value "
"specified. To enable, set to one (``1``)."
msgstr ""

# 1e3de2c9ee9041c2aa97f4ab946d1ef5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1114
msgid ""
"As connection to an origin server are opened, keep at least 'n' number of"
" connections open to that origin, even if the connection isn't used for a"
" long time period. Useful when the origin supports keep-alive, removing "
"the time needed to set up a new connection from the next request at the "
"expense of added (inactive) connections. To enable, set to one (``1``)."
msgstr ""

# d9313c4a89094176b842850e7623428c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1123
msgid ""
"The maximum number of failed connection attempts allowed before a round-"
"robin entry is marked as 'down' if a server has round-robin DNS entries."
msgstr ""

# 7dc2b68f041b47c6bcb6664049911240
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1130
msgid ""
"The timeout value (in seconds) for **time to first byte** for an origin "
"server connection."
msgstr ""

# 9e978d110fa04caa9af0adb276ea5d62
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1136
msgid ""
"The timeout value (in seconds) for an origin server connection when the "
"client request is a ``POST`` or ``PUT`` request."
msgstr ""

# 99375f8538c04ee8b7f90f1c5ace6bd3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1143
msgid ""
"Specifies how long (in seconds) Traffic Server remembers that an origin "
"server was unreachable."
msgstr ""

# 555c1649372e43db905b34158050266f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1149
msgid ""
"The number of seconds before Traffic Server marks an origin server as "
"unavailable after a client abandons a request because the origin server "
"was too slow in sending the response header."
msgstr ""

# f254368047a140e0a5f7702bd9194b28
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1154
msgid ""
"When enabled (1), Traffic Server bypasses the parent proxy for a request "
"that is not cacheable."
msgstr ""

# 1d507806dcd2420d9d66e2851c08ab74
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1157
msgid "Congestion Control"
msgstr ""

# 6c4de90717cc4b26b61c473ed21fc038
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1161
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) the Congestion Control option, which "
"configures Traffic Server to stop forwarding HTTP requests to origin "
"servers when they become congested. Traffic Server sends the client a "
"message to retry the congested origin server later. Refer to :ref:`using-"
"congestion-control`."
msgstr ""

# 263e03aef8d9419a9b6f4c7709fe6ae2
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1168
msgid ""
"Transaction buffering / flow control is enabled if this is set to a non-"
"zero value. Otherwise no flow control is done."
msgstr ""

# 315e3f1322ec44c2903d207ce388bc95
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1174
msgid ""
"The high water mark for transaction buffer control. External source I/O "
"is halted when the total buffer space in use by the transaction exceeds "
"this value."
msgstr ""

# 2977c75ac3b547eb8c50e0709e8250f5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1181
msgid ""
"The low water mark for transaction buffer control. External source I/O is"
" resumed when the total buffer space in use by the transaction is no more"
" than this value."
msgstr ""

# 0ea04510cc8f4fcf86de088a56c41221
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1187
msgid ""
"When enabled >= (``0``), Traffic Server will enforce a maximum number of "
"simultaneous websocket connections."
msgstr ""

# f98796c843cd4aada9b483c9b9b99778
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1190
msgid "Negative Response Caching"
msgstr ""

# 648756e9da084b5d89cbb41881a63c8b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1196
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server caches negative responses (such as "
"``404 Not Found``) when a requested page does not exist. The next time a "
"client requests the same page, Traffic Server serves the negative "
"response directly from cache. When disabled (``0``) Traffic Server will "
"only cache the response if the response has ``Cache-Control`` headers."
msgstr ""

# dc859d4d77f246bda1cc68220c74efa1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1202
msgid "The following negative responses are cached by Traffic Server:::"
msgstr ""

# 43e6be0f920a4e9fb07f92038fa173e0
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1216
msgid ""
"The cache lifetime for objects cached from this setting is controlled via"
" :ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.negative_caching_lifetime`."
msgstr ""

# 0f8d35bd09c34d6dbefe55e90b4e1113
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1222
msgid ""
"How long (in seconds) Traffic Server keeps the negative responses  valid "
"in cache. This value only affects negative responses that do NOT have "
"explicit ``Expires:`` or ``Cache-Control:`` lifetimes set by the server."
msgstr ""

# 7ec616a7b4434a1786ccdf73bbf0e9f1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1226
msgid "Proxy User Variables"
msgstr ""

# 321c7dee5764450a8bcfb6edbd66853b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1232
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server removes the ``From`` header to "
"protect the privacy of your users."
msgstr ""

# 50f980fdee6d4b338c1511e8b3cd8a61
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1237
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server removes the ``Referrer`` header to "
"protect the privacy of your site and users."
msgstr ""

# 4efc371ec2314e9eb32b10c929c35e1f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1243
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server removes the ``User-agent`` header to"
" protect the privacy of your site and users."
msgstr ""

# f9cc37f2911840f8aa6dd0421d02f6ab
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1249
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server removes the ``Cookie`` header to "
"protect the privacy of your site and users."
msgstr ""

# d4c31f0b4d0946bba690750846e0a704
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1255
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server removes ``Client-IP`` headers for "
"more privacy."
msgstr ""

# e7f994653bf346ad9a34745fbefe9d20
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1261
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server inserts ``Client-IP`` headers to "
"retain the client IP address."
msgstr ""

# 1f3aaf4e00ea4982b292d499c37d2c1b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1266
msgid ""
"Comma separated list of headers Traffic Server should remove from "
"outgoing requests."
msgstr ""

# 52dbb77ada20435d8c55c69d81712080
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1272
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server adds the client IP address to the "
"``X-Forwarded-For`` header."
msgstr ""

# e3b69f6c9f144e9680c2aa863b8f1424
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1278
msgid ""
"Enable (``1``) to normalize all ``Accept-Encoding:`` headers to one of "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

# f801fb56e4b34619a6a703d709ccefae
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1280
msgid ""
"``Accept-Encoding: gzip`` (if the header has ``gzip`` or ``x-gzip`` with "
"any ``q``) **OR**"
msgstr ""

# 79225e96d9ce4b61af28a3118d3b2ca7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1281
msgid "*blank* (for any header that does not include ``gzip``)"
msgstr ""

# 3ab39e4a88e342d49277469f43be87ea
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1283
msgid ""
"This is useful for minimizing cached alternates of documents (e.g. "
"``gzip, deflate`` vs. ``deflate, gzip``). Enabling this option is "
"recommended if your origin servers use no encodings other than ``gzip``."
msgstr ""

# 21c0e61157184664af14f6cb91642d1c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1287
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

# 7af195e60480492c9570ff75ba510f51
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1292
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) the HTTP ``PUSH`` option, which "
"allows you to deliver content directly to the cache without a user "
"request."
msgstr ""

# d228fcd88f8c4cbda36bd887de796873
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1297
msgid ""
"If you enable this option, then you must also specify a filtering rule in"
" the ip_allow.config file to allow only certain machines to push content "
"into the cache."
msgstr ""

# c9b538c0f98b48df8d8e3b931d705f21
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1304
msgid ""
"This feature is disabled by default with a value of (``0``), any positive"
" value will limit the size of post bodies. If a request is received with "
"a post body larger than this limit the response will be terminated with "
"413 - Request Entity Too Large and logged accordingly."
msgstr ""

# 282fbbb3161d4a149c056b3c40330b1e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1310
msgid "Cache Control"
msgstr ""

# 26d69953059d45e4ace834f96d8343c3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1315
msgid ""
"Specifies when to enable the ability to read a cached object while "
"another connection is completing the write to cache for that same object."
" The goal here is to avoid multiple origin connections for the same "
"cacheable object upon a cache miss. The possible values of this config "
"are:"
msgstr ""

# 7e64a98117d94b10a13f7d2994850cdc
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1320
msgid "``0`` = never read while writing"
msgstr ""

# d7ce6616654e4ec6bb826da1c98287dd
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1321
msgid "``1`` = always read while writing"
msgstr ""

# 985a1a6a0a6342d2b5f6377aae4fcc2d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1322
msgid ""
"``2`` = always read while writing, but allow non-cached Range requests "
"through to the origin"
msgstr ""

# 6ad36617ecdd45c3958b2bf5a78fbf57
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1324
msgid ""
"The ``2`` option is useful to avoid delaying requests which can not "
"easily be satisfied by the partially written response."
msgstr ""

# 82031db247dd488aa65d71719b0f42d3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1327
msgid ""
"Several other configuration values need to be set for this to be usable. "
"See :ref:`admin-configuration-reducing-origin-requests`."
msgstr ""

# f223137c7ed540edbb81c8ce8f85a383
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1333
msgid ""
"Specifies how many retries trafficserver attempts to trigger "
"read_while_writer on failing to obtain the write VC mutex or until the "
"first fragment is downloaded for the object being downloaded. The retry "
"duration is specified using the setting "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.cache.read_while_writer_retry.delay`"
msgstr ""

# ff81872eb08942f59aef2a314528c37d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1341
msgid ""
"Specifies the delay in msec, trafficserver waits to reattempt "
"read_while_writer on failing to obtain the write VC mutex or until the "
"first fragment is downloaded for the object being downloaded. Note that "
"trafficserver implements a progressive delay in reattempting, by doubling"
" the configured duration from the third reattempt onwards."
msgstr ""

# d061f0af6c464867bd9b61b4389382f7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1350
msgid ""
"Forces the use of a specific hardware sector size, e.g. 4096, for all "
"disks."
msgstr ""

# 65daf2d2acf846ec872f96dfe960e8c7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1352
msgid ""
"SSDs and \"advanced format” drives claim a sector size of 512; however, "
"it is safe to force a higher size than the hardware supports natively as "
"we count atomicity in 512 byte increments."
msgstr ""

# f024354e94a44ae3ab9003dfecf6c590
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1355
msgid ""
"4096-sized drives formatted for Windows will have partitions aligned on "
"63 512-byte sector boundaries, so they will be unaligned. There are "
"workarounds, but you need to do some research on your particular drive. "
"Some drives have a one-time option to switch the partition boundary, "
"while others might require reformatting or repartitioning."
msgstr ""

# f49cbd10b53b45f8b1c7c4cef2eb666c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1360
msgid ""
"To be safe in Linux, you could just use the entire drive: ``/dev/sdb`` "
"instead of ``/dev/sdb1`` and Traffic Server will do the right thing. "
"Misaligned partitions on Linux are auto-detected."
msgstr ""

# e3d4362e516b4f8c91b09aa671e93c45
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1363
msgid ""
"For example: If ``/sys/block/sda/sda1/alignment_offset`` is non-zero, ATS"
" will offset reads/writes to that disk by that alignment. If Linux knows "
"about any existing partition misalignments, ATS will compensate."
msgstr ""

# 14f5d491dc3b4bfa878a5c69fa89d7ff
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1366
msgid ""
"Partitions formatted to support hardware sector size of more than 512 "
"(e.g. 4096) will result in all objects stored in the cache to be integral"
" multiples of 4096 bytes, which will result in some waste for small "
"files."
msgstr ""

# af54c28f4c7c426b89eef069a6f309e7
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1374
msgid "Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) caching of HTTP requests."
msgstr ""

# cc2b5aa76e0a4dd6b8fe9fd3fcb8026c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1380
msgid ""
"If set to a value other than ``-1``, the value if this configuration "
"option is combined with the cache key at cache lookup time. Changing this"
" value has the effect of an instantaneous, zero-cost cache purge since it"
" will cause all subsequent cache keys to change. Since this is an "
"overrideable configuration, it can be used to purge the entire cache, or "
"just a specific :file:`remap.config` rule."
msgstr ""

# 3feb14077f2e4515adb7413c1d3fbef1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1392
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) caching objects that have an empty "
"response body. This is particularly useful for caching 301 or 302 "
"responses with a ``Location`` header but no document body. This only "
"works if the origin response also has a ``Content-Length`` header."
msgstr ""

# fff144f9ba324dcd9825afdf402bf3c8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1401
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server ignores client requests to bypass "
"the cache."
msgstr ""

# 8b924f8c880f45b0866f0fe1e8bbf2f1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1407
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server issues a conditional request to the "
"origin server if an incoming request has a ``No-Cache`` header."
msgstr ""

# fafd8694b3bf44d29412523b3a0dfcac
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1413
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server ignores origin server requests to "
"bypass the cache."
msgstr ""

# 07e3fa3900674933b155173480082c1d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1419
msgid "Specifies how cookies are cached:"
msgstr ""

# c744eb407fb54be387d9f09230785237
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1421
msgid "``0`` = do not cache any responses to cookies"
msgstr ""

# 2006542b8dae48d88c03bb6960e8eaa8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1422
msgid "``1`` = cache for any content-type"
msgstr ""

# f13796f317404f4293418a915f935575
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1423
msgid "``2`` = cache only for image types"
msgstr ""

# ec66d146a4a74d298a9d987a4974767a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1424
msgid "``3`` = cache for all but text content-types"
msgstr ""

# ecaec3d1ce3d4aaa82750c13b38d93c1
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1429
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server ignores ``WWW-Authentication`` "
"headers in responses ``WWW-Authentication`` headers are removed and not "
"cached."
msgstr ""

# 9cf70afbff4944eaaa0aab381b3fba3a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1436
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) caching of URLs that look dynamic, "
"i.e.: URLs that end in ``.asp`` or contain a question mark (``?``), a "
"semicolon (``;``), or ``cgi``. For a full list, please refer to "
"`HttpTransact::url_looks_dynamic </link/to/doxygen>`_"
msgstr ""

# ed7f54efef034f6a89b2defd2ad46f71
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1443
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) caching of alternate versions of HTTP"
" objects that do not contain the ``Vary`` header."
msgstr ""

# 3030b076b3f24595a0e36e78b6a19293
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1449
msgid "Specifies when to revalidate content:"
msgstr ""

# 7acc6c357efd4d72bc18fcbf10895ec9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1451
msgid "``0`` = use cache directives or heuristic (the default value)"
msgstr ""

# 998272bec3b8467cbd72e30aed5bdc8e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1452
msgid "``1`` = stale if heuristic"
msgstr ""

# 634f4d2f0fdc42ca91dfe4c806c81025
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1453
msgid "``2`` = always stale (always revalidate)"
msgstr ""

# bb71de790b6545af9e557cf3d4dfd1ec
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1454
msgid "``3`` = never stale"
msgstr ""

# 02236aa2ee9f4913b6e597b75ed7c5b3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1456
msgid "``4`` = use cache directives or heuristic (0) unless the request"
msgstr ""

# c801ac2280454af0bac1ec302dcea578
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1456
msgid "has an ``If-Modified-Since`` header"
msgstr ""

# b356fcac9b954a19b41145dae9ce3c0f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1458
msgid ""
"If the request contains the ``If-Modified-Since`` header, then Traffic "
"Server always revalidates the cached content and uses the client's ``If-"
"Modified-Since`` header for the proxy request."
msgstr ""

# 6e4c04e64a8f45c29e8daf08082e3bbb
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1466
msgid "The type of headers required in a request for the request to be cacheable."
msgstr ""

# 7a8010c0752b4ec69b5f0320746c817f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1468
msgid "``0`` = no headers required to make document cacheable"
msgstr ""

# a766916685474e758deed9b2f7047c66
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1469
msgid ""
"``1`` = either the ``Last-Modified`` header, or an explicit lifetime "
"header, ``Expires`` or ``Cache-Control: max-age``, is required"
msgstr ""

# a2fdd153ec484114b03e9a9c151744a8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1470
msgid ""
"``2`` = explicit lifetime is required, ``Expires`` or ``Cache-Control: "
"max-age``"
msgstr ""

# 0ae887d31829473bb6cfcc0a175b3d7d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1476
msgid "The maximum age allowed for a stale response before it cannot be cached."
msgstr ""

# 320e43b76bd94ba0a4a5c5139acf951c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1481
msgid "When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server looks up range requests in the cache."
msgstr ""

# 4d212e464f2b40558e8e1e8138a4d60a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1486
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server will attempt to write (lock) the URL"
" to cache. This is rarely useful (at the moment), since it'll only be "
"able to write to cache if the origin has ignored the ``Range:`` header. "
"For a use case where you know the origin will respond with a full "
"(``200``) response, you can turn this on to allow it to be cached."
msgstr ""

# 0fef35d872f342678b30c43597a76467
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1495
msgid ""
"When enabled with a value of ``1``, Traffic Server serves documents from "
"cache with a ``Content-Type:`` header even if it does not match the "
"``Accept:`` header of the request. If set to ``2`` (default), this logic "
"only happens in the absence of a ``Vary`` header in the cached response "
"(which is the recommended and safe use)."
msgstr ""

# 1ffc9aaf56bc495480f8bb5372e2e8c9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1501
msgid ""
"This option should only be enabled with ``1`` if you're having problems "
"with caching *and* you origin server doesn't set the ``Vary`` header. "
"Alternatively, if the origin is incorrectly setting ``Vary: Accept`` or "
"doesn't respond with ``406 (Not Acceptable)``, you can also enable this "
"configuration with a ``1``."
msgstr ""

# 8f12833379eb4381991f82dc5a1f5812
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1510
msgid ""
"When enabled with a value of ``1``, Traffic Server serves documents from "
"cache with a ``Content-Language:`` header even if it does not match the "
"``Accept-Language:`` header of the request. If set to ``2`` (default), "
"this logic only happens in the absence of a ``Vary`` header in the cached"
" response (which is the recommended and safe use)."
msgstr ""

# 7de5848faa854c78afadfa5cee4be77a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1517
msgid ""
"This option should only be enabled with ``1`` if you're having problems "
"with caching *and* you origin server doesn't set the ``Vary`` header. "
"Alternatively, if the origin is incorrectly setting ``Vary: Accept-"
"Language`` or doesn't respond with ``406 (Not Acceptable)``, you can also"
" enable this configuration with a ``1``."
msgstr ""

# 821aec2f5f194efcb0cc2f769b469735
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1526
msgid ""
"When enabled with a value of ``1``, Traffic Server serves documents from "
"cache with a ``Content-Encoding:`` header even if it does not match the "
"``Accept-Encoding:`` header of the request. If set to ``2`` (default), "
"this logic only happens in the absence of a ``Vary`` header in the cached"
" response (which is the recommended and safe use)."
msgstr ""

# 0c116501cf83495ea90700932eebaa5d
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1533
msgid ""
"This option should only be enabled with ``1`` if you're having problems "
"with caching *and* you origin server doesn't set the ``Vary`` header. "
"Alternatively, if the origin is incorrectly setting ``Vary: Accept-"
"Encoding`` or doesn't respond with ``406 (Not Acceptable)`` you can also "
"enable this configuration with a ``1``."
msgstr ""

# 6031e5f233b2411baa6dae44f1318aac
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1542
msgid ""
"When enabled with a value of ``1``, Traffic Server serves documents from "
"cache with a ``Content-Type:`` header even if it does not match the "
"``Accept-Charset:`` header of the request. If set to ``2`` (default), "
"this logic only happens in the absence of a ``Vary`` header in the cached"
" response (which is the recommended and safe use)."
msgstr ""

# f2fcd4e4049e41438c90a24e886a3261
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1549
msgid ""
"This option should only be enabled with ``1`` if you're having problems "
"with caching *and* you origin server doesn't set the ``Vary`` header. "
"Alternatively, if the origin is incorrectly setting ``Vary: Accept-"
"Charset`` or doesn't respond with ``406 (Not Acceptable)``, you can also "
"enable this configuration with a ``1``."
msgstr ""

# 8f95b7bab25b4b049ab942a8e7775b68
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1559
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server ignores any ``Cache-Control: max-"
"age`` headers from the client. This technically violates the HTTP RFC, "
"but avoids a problem where a client can forcefully invalidate a cached "
"object."
msgstr ""

# d586e9161aab4687bb838a0789b750a6
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1565
msgid "Specifies the maximum object size that will be cached. ``0`` is unlimited."
msgstr ""

# cccc1623952c4105b35e5644c5c2eebf
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1570
msgid ""
"When enabled (``1``), Traffic Server will keep certain HTTP objects in "
"the cache for a certain time as specified in cache.config."
msgstr ""

# 8a7bd830e1e240419ccd57291be6e329
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1574
msgid ""
"The size of the region (as a percentage of the total content storage in a"
" :term:`cache stripe`) in front of the :term:`write cursor` that "
"constitutes a recent access hit for evacutating the accessed object."
msgstr ""

# 0d9d714cb0304b3da5e5071746a4c97c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1577
msgid ""
"When an object is accessed it can be marked for evacuation, that is to be"
" copied over the write cursor and thereby preserved from being "
"overwritten. This is done if it is no more than a specific number of "
"bytes in front of the write cursor. The number of bytes is a percentage "
"of the total number of bytes of content storage in the cache stripe where"
" the object is stored and that percentage is set by this variable."
msgstr ""

# 59ce2ba46e384924a07f80cb2aaca640
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1582
msgid "By default, the feature is off (set to 0)."
msgstr ""

# ebe9ab393dfb4a048b8879ef633cd231
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1587
msgid "Limit the size of objects that are hit evacuated."
msgstr ""

# ac6a85e3a2ad4433b8d46e66ed5fcad3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1589
msgid ""
"Objects larger than the limit are not hit evacuated. A value of 0 "
"disables the limit."
msgstr ""

# 3fc64bd91d624cbdac1edf4398c862a9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1593
msgid ""
"The maximum number of alternates that are allowed for any given URL. "
"Disable by setting to 0."
msgstr ""

# 1ddd19d9fdd64755a8970e9388d7dc03
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1598
msgid ""
"Sets the target size of a contiguous fragment of a file in the disk "
"cache. When setting this, consider that larger numbers could waste memory"
" on slow connections, but smaller numbers could increase (waste) seeks."
msgstr ""

# fab66be5391a401dba576460f25337a6
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1603
msgid "RAM Cache"
msgstr ""

# 68867eb2009c40dea38d98fa85e37c94
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1607
msgid ""
"By default the RAM cache size is automatically determined, based on disk "
"cache size; approximately 10 MB of RAM cache per GB of disk cache. "
"Alternatively, it can be set to a fixed value such as **20GB** "
"(21474836480)"
msgstr ""

# 4b4435a9a13e4c7bafc1115992ebdd55
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1614
msgid ""
"Objects greater than this size will not be kept in the RAM cache. This "
"should be set high enough to keep objects accessed frequently in memory "
"in order to improve performance. **4MB** (4194304)"
msgstr ""

# b465df38b5ef427f9c685f9ffe31398c
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1621
msgid ""
"Two distinct RAM caches are supported, the default (0) being the "
"**CLFUS** (*Clocked Least Frequently Used by Size*). As an alternative, a"
" simpler **LRU** (*Least Recently Used*) cache is also available, by "
"changing this configuration to 1."
msgstr ""

# c1a00b57c5654e85b2722553b75c7b49
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1628
msgid ""
"Enabling this option will filter inserts into the RAM cache to ensure "
"that they have been seen at least once.  For the **LRU**, this provides "
"scan resistance. Note that **CLFUS** already requires that a document "
"have history before it is inserted, so for **CLFUS**, setting this option"
" means that a document must be seen three times before it is added to the"
" RAM cache."
msgstr ""

# a41ebb4d70a040d5834de4cd97c8cb28
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1636
msgid ""
"The **CLFUS** RAM cache also supports an optional in-memory compression. "
"This is not to be confused with ``Content-Encoding: gzip`` compression. "
"The RAM cache compression is intended to try to save space in the RAM, "
"and is not visible to the User-Agent (client)."
msgstr ""

# 4641496adf684ae2a3ac5e5b26bb085a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1641
msgid "Possible values are:"
msgstr ""

# d806a9b661a64eca864f3ce8eb1afc84
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1643
msgid "``0`` = no compression"
msgstr ""

# a493dbe07ae749aea1fc4aa3bb3c8196
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1644
msgid "``1`` = fastlz (extremely fast, relatively low compression)"
msgstr ""

# 00e63f91d50742ffbced7be5b3d8aa50
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1645
msgid "``2`` = libz (moderate speed, reasonable compression)"
msgstr ""

# 4ec7778a66474b67a1758799144a4841
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1646
msgid "``3`` = liblzma (very slow, high compression)"
msgstr ""

# c9140288fba248d3978175cd4600073f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1650
msgid ""
"Compression runs on task threads.  To use more cores for RAM cache "
"compression, increase :ts:cv:`proxy.config.task_threads`."
msgstr ""

# 4e2aa00caec2492c9224fecc959ec40e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1653
msgid "Heuristic Expiration"
msgstr ""

# 905b4ffbc3f141749b317f6f1fc9cda4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1659
msgid ""
"The minimum amount of time an HTTP object without an expiration date can "
"remain fresh in the cache before is considered to be stale."
msgstr ""

# 78aece8ce444443fa4601fa39dbb15d4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1666
msgid ""
"The maximum amount of time an HTTP object without an expiration date can "
"remain fresh in the cache before is considered to be stale."
msgstr ""

# b4ae546444d64286b3f4d9f9f80c780a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1673
msgid ""
"The aging factor for freshness computations. Traffic Server stores an "
"object for this percentage of the time that elapsed since it last "
"changed."
msgstr ""

# 7860ce4f2ba648909f1313b87b9e22ca
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1680
msgid ""
"How often Traffic Server checks for an early refresh, during the period "
"before the document stale time. The interval specified must be in "
"seconds. See :ref:`fuzzy-revalidation`"
msgstr ""

# 58a353fdf77c45c6b322a97ccfeff852
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1687
msgid ""
"The probability that a refresh is made on a document during the specified"
" fuzz time."
msgstr ""

# 3fb30d0aefe34762a40303cd580ed937
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1693
msgid ""
"Handles requests with a TTL less than fuzz.time – it allows for different"
" times to evaluate the probability of revalidation for small TTLs and big"
" TTLs. Objects with small TTLs will start \"rolling the revalidation "
"dice\" near the fuzz.min_time, while objects with large TTLs would start "
"at fuzz.time. A logarithmic like function between determines the "
"revalidation evaluation start time (which will be between fuzz.min_time "
"and fuzz.time). As the object gets closer to expiring, the window start "
"becomes more likely. By default this setting is not enabled, but should "
"be enabled anytime you have objects with small TTLs. The default value is"
" ``0``."
msgstr ""

# 7b1ba3ccda754f86b769b679edca1c96
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1696
msgid "Dynamic Content & Content Negotiation"
msgstr ""

# 18e68384817a480ebcb8d3d029814985
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1701
msgid "The header on which Traffic Server varies for text documents."
msgstr ""

# 4664f9c7e30d4390a3107f6093bf594b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1703
msgid ""
"For example: if you specify ``User-agent``, then Traffic Server caches "
"all the different user-agent versions of documents it encounters."
msgstr ""

# 86404482932342dbb5504f7beb5718a0
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1709
msgid "The header on which Traffic Server varies for images."
msgstr ""

# 267de89480164df6af1376374330a583
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1714
msgid ""
"The header on which Traffic Server varies for anything other than text "
"and images."
msgstr ""

# 709e8da288204322baa530a2cddecfad
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1719
msgid ""
"The number of milliseconds a cacheable request will wait before "
"requesting the object from cache if an equivalent request is in flight."
msgstr ""

# 1e1f01b008264a4b95bd2c1475567747
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1724
msgid ""
"The number of times to attempt fetching an object from cache if there was"
" an equivalent request in flight."
msgstr ""

# d6b2f123e6514b87a0c39f67053e5208
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1729
msgid ""
"The number of times to attempt a cache open write upon failure to get a "
"write lock."
msgstr ""

# 9ee772f8b17a4a5da6d7c3d2510bd803
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1734
msgid ""
"This setting indicates the action taken on failing to obtain the cache "
"open write lock on either a cache miss or a cache hit stale. This "
"typically happens when there is more than one request to the same cache "
"object simultaneously. During such a scenario, all but one (which goes to"
" the origin) request is served either a stale copy or an error depending "
"on this setting."
msgstr ""

# dea1fdd10eae4000ab7c7ddf9fec4851
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1739
msgid "``0`` = default, disable cache and goto origin server"
msgstr ""

# dd8a162c905a4e0bb8efc63b61b55160
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1740
msgid "``1`` = return a 502 error on a cache miss"
msgstr ""

# 899e7cd2bc38492d90bc22eddeca1ec5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1741
msgid ""
"``2`` = serve stale if object's age is under "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.cache.max_stale_age`, else, goto origin server"
msgstr ""

# eb2939b39c71410c8bdf9b5378cc42dd
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1742
msgid ""
"``3`` = return a 502 error on a cache miss or serve stale on a cache "
"revalidate"
msgstr ""

# 99a4053eb6bd471dae7ece99e7ed687e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1743
msgid ""
"if object's age is under :ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.cache.max_stale_age`, "
"else, goto origin server"
msgstr ""

# 6587098a2aef49a69787638dd9b86ae8
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1744
msgid "``4`` = return a 502 error on either a cache miss or on a revalidate"
msgstr ""

# bf9467954c6a4ae98bbb4bb2e46a4c23
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1747
msgid "Customizable User Response Pages"
msgstr ""

# ba675eb67194466c86a2522d82efe456
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1751
msgid ""
"Specifies whether customizable response pages are language specific or "
"not:"
msgstr ""

# 787b3a70561c45a5867eb3af05b10d64
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1754
msgid ""
"``1`` = enable customizable user response pages in the default directory "
"only"
msgstr ""

# 9ba47aa0a81b40bd9a1f80d841791cb4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1755
msgid "``2`` = enable language-targeted user response pages"
msgstr ""

# aec80caa40034023ba64328ce8278494
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1756
msgid "``3`` = enable host-targeted user response pages"
msgstr ""

# da19e81a9fce46a8bb870c38867ae601
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1760
msgid ""
"Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) logging for customizable response "
"pages. When enabled, Traffic Server records a message in the error log "
"each time a customized response page is used or modified."
msgstr ""

# b9769c15dc0e4d4d8da456705dc41b45
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1765
msgid ""
"The customizable response page default directory. If this is a relative "
"path, Traffic Server resolves it relative to the ``PREFIX`` directory."
msgstr ""

# 699b47845e2346c0b1357f9137930c27
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1773
msgid ""
"A prefix for the file name to use to find an error template file. If set "
"(not the empty string) this value and an underscore are predended to the "
"file name to find in the template sets directory. See :ref:`body-"
"factory`."
msgstr ""

# d7e58833be644b8bb3f742f5ea40daae
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1779
msgid "Specifies when Traffic Server suppresses generated response pages:"
msgstr ""

# 3db80949adc843a4af7652f79235e148
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1781
msgid "``0`` = never suppress generated response pages"
msgstr ""

# 38345f59c6b146f5b660f29a7dfffae5
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1782
msgid "``1`` = always suppress generated response pages"
msgstr ""

# 37b5202daec54142893a06ae516443d9
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1783
msgid "``2`` = suppress response pages only for intercepted traffic"
msgstr ""

# ab258a3232054acd9f0a6a9731b74c50
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1787
msgid "Specifies which http UI endpoints to allow within :file:`remap.config`:"
msgstr ""

# 2edf15caafd84f9182e3179669bf43ae
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1789
msgid "``0`` = disable all http UI endpoints"
msgstr ""

# eadca1f00fc24f1c8955b38eb9dadfab
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1790
msgid "``1`` = enable only cache endpoints"
msgstr ""

# d5495137d0cd44e28c38c23dc6da8908
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1791
msgid "``2`` = enable only stats endpoints"
msgstr ""

# 035e926c5f014895b46d92587208c7cc
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1792
msgid "``3`` = enable all http UI endpoints"
msgstr ""

# f21e977e9e204dfaa6bebb90f3ff6ebc
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1794
msgid ""
"To enable any enpoint there needs to be an entry in :file:`remap.config` "
"which specifically enables it. Such a line would look like: ::"
msgstr ""

# 06aa2dbd48ad4dd5a36ccd470ed17643
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1799
msgid "The following are the cache endpoints:"
msgstr ""

# 8a1bdaadc78d4d64b513c1a53b6ceab6
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1801
msgid "``cache`` = UI to interact with the cache"
msgstr ""

# 4ac43e9305c6487dbd39db87cb4f7ad2
