"Traffic Server refers to the :file:`splitdns.config` file for the "
"selection specification. Refer to :ref:`Configuring DNS Server Selection "
"<admin-split-dns>`."
msgstr ""

# 41c7c3b81d024b06a0da8d94cac8d292
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1841
msgid ""
"Specifies a list of hostname extensions that are automatically added to "
"the hostname after a failed lookup. For example: if you want Traffic "
"Server to add the hostname extension .org, then specify ``org`` as the "
"value for this variable (Traffic Server automatically adds the dot (.))."
msgstr ""

# 2c87b01074bc430c804f992357eb331a
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1847
msgid ""
"If the variable :ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.enable_url_expandomatic` is set"
" to ``1`` (the default value), then you do not have to add ``www.`` and "
"``.com`` to this list because Traffic Server automatically tries www. and"
" .com after trying the values you've specified."
msgstr ""

# 09a6252609974f6d8a07d45c2754fccf
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1853
msgid ""
"Allows to specify which ``resolv.conf`` file to use for finding "
"resolvers. While the format of this file must be the same as the standard"
" ``resolv.conf`` file, this option allows an administrator to manage the "
"set of resolvers in an external configuration file, without affecting how"
" the rest of the operating system uses DNS."
msgstr ""

# 734dc93b7db9449482aed865c47a893e
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1860
msgid "Enables (``1``) or disables (``0``) DNS server round-robin."
msgstr ""

# d6bd9d187a6947b2a4379b8d44d3b0da
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1865
msgid "The DNS servers."
msgstr ""

# 961b1aa6c05b4d5b864ad9d340958323
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1870
msgid "Indicates whether to use SRV records for orgin server lookup."
msgstr ""

# cf4cfc6c794143bdb18a6d98c95403f4
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1874
msgid ""
"Create and dedicate a thread entirely for DNS processing. This is "
"probably most useful on system which do a significant number of DNS "
"lookups, typically forward proxies. But even on other systems, it can "
"avoid some contention on the first worker thread (which otherwise takes "
"on the burden of all DNS lookups)."
msgstr ""

# dc258f0d772946f39a243774d4a4b640
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1882
msgid ""
"When enabled (1) provides additional resilience against DNS forgery (for "
"instance in DNS Injection attacks), particularly in forward or "
"transparent proxies, but requires that the resolver populates the queries"
" section of the response properly."
msgstr ""

# 14cee616432a4c4c97aa9ec5e3ba4dbe
#: ../../admin-guide/files/records.config.en.rst:1887
msgid "HostDB"
msgstr ""

